      "span_text": "Liver catalase (CAT) was determined by Goth's colorimetric method, in which supernatant was incubated in H 2 O 2 substrate and the enzymatic reaction was stopped by the addition of ammonium molybdate. The intensity of the yellow complex formed by molybdate and H 2 O 2 was measured at 405 nm [CITATION_1] ."
